      <div class="section-heading">
        <h2>Frequently asked questions</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="faq">

        <details>
          <summary>What is the difference between the GTM Score and the Intelligence Report?</summary>
          <p>
            The GTM Score is a free and lightweight diagnostic. It quantifies your GTM system and 
            shows where friction sits. The Intelligence Report is a deeper GRIP analysis. It reveals 
            the constraints behind the score, explains why they exist and prioritises where improvement 
            will have the highest return.
          </p>
        </details>

        <details>
          <summary>How long does the assessment take?</summary>
          <p>
            The assessment contains 265 questions and takes approximately 45 minutes to complete. 
            Progress is saved automatically, so you can pause and resume. Most leadership teams 
            complete it in one sitting.
          </p>
        </details>

        <details>
          <summary>When do I receive my report?</summary>
          <p>
            Your complete Intelligence Report is delivered within five working days after you 
            complete the assessment. The report is generated using AI-assisted analysis and reviewed 
            for quality before delivery.
          </p>
        </details>

        <details>
          <summary>What format is the report delivered in?</summary>
          <p>
            The report is delivered as a structured PDF document (typically 40+ pages). It includes 
            your scores, GRIP Diamond analysis, archetype classification, priority roadmap and 
            implementation guidance.
          </p>
        </details>

        <details>
          <summary>Can I share this with my team?</summary>
          <p>
            Yes. The report is designed to be shared with your leadership team and used as a 
            foundation for strategic discussions. Many companies use it to align executive teams 
            and board members.
          </p>
